gantt
preheat oven to 300, grease pans :a, 2010-01-01, 1d
section sponge
    finely chop 3oz semi-sweet chocolate and combine with 1 1/2cups hot coffee, stir, let stand until melted and smooth :b, 2010-01-01, 3d
    sift 3cups sugar,  2 1/2cups flour, 1 1/2 cups cocoa, 2tsp baking soda, 3/4tsp baking powder, and 1 1/4tsp salt :c, 2010-01-01, 2d
    With electric mixer, beat 3 eggs until thickened :e1, 2010-01-01, 2d
    Slowly add 3/4cup oil, 1 1/2cups buttermilk, 3/4tsp vanilla and melted chocolate mixture to eggs :e, after e1, 2d
    add sugar mixture and beat on medium until well combined :f, after e c, 1d
    put in oven :g, after a f, 1d
    bake until tester comes out clean, 1hr to 1hr 10mins :crit, h, after g, 60d
section frosting
    Finely chop 1lb semisweet chocolate :i, after g, 1d
    boil 1cup cream, 2tbsp sugar, 2tbsp corn syrup over moderately low heat, whisking until sugar is dissolved :j, after g, 2d
    Remove from heat, whisk in 1lb chocolate until melted :k, after i j, 1d
    Cut butter into pieces and add one at a time, whisking until smooth :l, after k, 1d
    cool cake and frosting until spreadable :crit, m, after l h, 20d
section assemble
    spread frosting between layers and over top and sides, :z, after m h, 1d
    DONE :zz, after z, 1d
&&&
**Cake Layers**
3oz semi-sweet chocolate (like Callebaut)
1 1/2cups hot brewed coffee
3cups sugar
2 1/2cups all-purpose flour
1 1/2cups unsweetened cocoa powder (not dutch process)
2tsp baking soda
3/4tsp baking powder
1 1/4tsp salt
3 large eggs
3/4cup vegetable oil
1 1/2cups buttermilk (well shaken)
3/4tsp vanilla
**Frosting**
1lb semisweet chocolate
1cup heavy cream
2tbsp sugar
2tbsp light corn syrup
1/2stick (1/4cup) unsalted butter
